Lim Jae-Suk (born November 9, 1979 in Seoul, South Korea), often anglicised to Jae-Suk Lim, is a South Korean middleweight mixed martial artist and is the current Spirit MC Middleweight Champion.[3] Lim has fought for Strikeforce, Elite XC, and Spirit MC. He made his American MMA debut at EliteXC: Renegade with a 1st round submission over Daniel Pineda. Lim spent time in the South Korean Army in the special forces and learned many martial arts during his time there. After his time in the Army, Lim trained kickboxing and spent time as a kickboxer.[4] It was not until 2003 he started his MMA career. Lim retired from MMA in 2009 to spend more time with his family.
